/wiki/Carl_Cort: Carl Edward Richard Cort (born 1 November 1977) is a former footballer who last played as a forward for Tampa Bay Rowdies in the North American Soccer League.
Wolverhampton Wanderers Football Club /ˌwʊlvərˈhæmptən/ (listen), commonly known as Wolves, is an English professional football club based in Wolverhampton, West Midlands. Formed as St. Luke's FC in 1877, the club has played at Molineux Stadium since 1889 and competes in the Premier League, the top division of English football, after winning the 2017–18 EFL Championship. The Wolves also compete in the 2019–20 UEFA Europa League: this is the first time the club has qualified for a European tournament for 39 years, by virtue of finishing in seventh place in the 2018–19 Premier League, their first season in the top tier since  the 2011–12 season.
/wiki/Bryan_Deasley_(footballer): Bryan Deasley (born 29 June 1988) is a Scottish professional footballer who plays for Lochee United.
Dundee Football Club is a professional football club based in the city of Dundee, Scotland. Founded in 1893, they are nicknamed "The Dark Blues" or "The Dee". The club plays its home matches at Dens Park.
/wiki/Stuart_Duff: Stuart Duff (born 23 January 1982 in Aberdeen) is a retired Scottish professional football player who last played for Inverurie Loco Works in the Highland Football League. He was primarily a central midfielder although his versatility saw him play in most defensive and midfield positions.
Dundee United Football Club is a Scottish professional football club based in the city of Dundee. Formed in 1909. originally as Dundee Hibernian, the club changed to the present name in 1923. United are nicknamed The Terrors or The Tangerines and the supporters are known as Arabs.
/wiki/Rob_Edwards_(footballer_born_1982): Robert Owen "Rob" Edwards (born 25 December 1982) is a professional football manager and former player. Edwards played as a centre back and is currently a coach with the England U20 squad.
/wiki/James_Grady: James Grady (born 14 March 1971 in Paisley) is a Scottish former footballer who spent the majority of his career in the top two divisions in Scottish football. He played as a striker, and became player/manager for Greenock Morton in the First Division between 2009 and 2010.
/wiki/Garry_Kenneth: Garry Kenneth (born 21 June 1987) is a Scottish former footballer, who played as a centre back for Dundee United, Cowdenbeath, Bristol Rovers, Brechin City, Carnoustie Panmure, Adamstown Rosebud and Skonto Riga. He also represented Scotland twice at full international level.
/wiki/Mark_Kerr_(footballer): Mark Kerr (born 2 March 1982) is a Scottish professional football player and coach, who is the player-manager of Scottish Championship side Ayr United.
/wiki/Lee_Miller_(footballer): Lee Adamson Miller (born 18 May 1983) is a Scottish football player and coach. Miller played as a striker for Falkirk (two spells), Bristol City, Hearts, Dundee United, Aberdeen, Middlesbrough, Notts County, Scunthorpe, Carlisle, Kilmarnock and Livingston.
/wiki/Lee_Peacock: Lee Anthony Peacock (born 9 October 1976) is a Scottish former professional footballer and Head of Youth Coaching at Swindon Town.
Sheffield Wednesday Football Club is a professional association football club based in Sheffield, England. The team competes in the Championship, the second tier of the English football league system. Formed in 1867 as an offshoot of The Wednesday Cricket Club (itself formed in 1820), they went by the name of the Wednesday Football Club until changing to their current name in 1929.
